Quote: Neenish Tarts.[This recipe uses raspberry jam in the filling and raspberry coloured icing in place of chocolate. The only recognisable constituent is having a circular iced top in two colours - in this case, white and pink.
Notes: So far no further NZ recipe books have turned it up and it looks as though the 60s might be about the earliest printed occurrence, but I haven't given up hope yet. I have now been through the Turnbull's five boxes without luck.

